<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="M4" checkit-title="Finding a matrix inverse">
  <statement>
    <p>Show how to find the inverse of the matrix <m>N= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
-1 &amp; 1 &amp; -2 &amp; -3 \\
1 &amp; -2 &amp; 4 &amp; 3 \\
-1 &amp; 2 &amp; -3 &amp; -4 \\
0 &amp; -2 &amp; 7 &amp; -2
\end{array}\right] </m>.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>N^{-1}= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
4 &amp; 14 &amp; 9 &amp; -3 \\
-5 &amp; -9 &amp; -4 &amp; 2 \\
-2 &amp; -4 &amp; -2 &amp; 1 \\
-2 &amp; -5 &amp; -3 &amp; 1
\end{array}\right] </me>
  </answer>
</exercise>

